`Not allowed to start service Intent ... without permission not exported from uid 10205`

Does this mean that script starting is not implemented, not allowed due to security reasons, or something else?

It is no problem to prompt the user to launch the robot manually, but i like simplicity, and most of the users wont be terminal-heads, and this seemed a very good solution.

(launching code)
```java
    public void launchRobot() {
        File file = new File("/data/data/com.termux/files/usr/bin/node");
        Uri scriptUri = new Uri.Builder().scheme("com.termux.file").path(file.getAbsolutePath()).build();

        Intent executeIntent = new Intent(ACTION_EXECUTE, scriptUri);
        executeIntent.setClassName("com.termux", TERMUX_SERVICE);
        executeIntent.putExtra(EXTRA_EXECUTE_IN_BACKGROUND, true);
        executeIntent.putExtra(EXTRA_CURRENT_WORKING_DIRECTORY, "/data/data/com.termux/files/home/robot/");
        executeIntent.putExtra(EXTRA_ARGUMENTS, new String[]{"main.js"});

        Intent wakeLockIntent = new Intent("com.termux.service_wake_lock");
        wakeLockIntent.setClassName("com.termux", TERMUX_SERVICE);

        startService(executeIntent);
        startService(wakeLockIntent);
    }
```

