seems like i have same issue as #141, and here's a simple program that reproduces it:

```go
package main

import (
	"io"
	"log"
	"net/http"
	"os"
)

func main() {
	resp, err := http.Get("https://google.com")
	if err != nil {
		log.Printf("oops: %v", err)
		return
	}
	defer resp.Body.Close()
	io.Copy(os.Stdout, resp.Body)
}
```

the error states that udp connection on port 53 was refused.

